{
  "id": "goodman-gsx13-refrigerant",
  "brand": "Goodman",
  "model": "GSX130361",
  "equipment_type": "ac-condenser",
  "symptom": "Unit runs constantly but house won't cool below 80\u00b0F. Suction line is warm, not sweating. Liquid line feels hot. Possible hissing near the service valve or coil.",
  "diagnosis": "Low R-410A charge due to slow leak \u2014 likely at the service valve Schrader core or a brazed joint on the evaporator coil. Subcooling will read low (<5\u00b0F vs. 10\u201312\u00b0F spec), superheat high (>20\u00b0F).",
  "part_number": "R-410A refrigerant (sold by weight) + leak sealant if pinhole, or coil replacement if severe",
  "procedure": [
    "Connect gauges to the high and low service ports with a manifold set rated for R-410A (660 PSI burst).",
    "Record suction pressure and liquid pressure. Expected: ~118 PSI suction / ~350 PSI liquid at 95\u00b0F ambient.",
    "Calculate subcooling (condenser sat temp minus liquid line temp) and superheat (suction line temp minus evaporator sat temp).",
    "If subcooling < 5\u00b0F and superheat > 15\u00b0F, unit is undercharged.",
    "Perform a nitrogen leak test: isolate the system, pressurize to 150 PSI with dry nitrogen, soap-bubble all joints and Schrader cores.",
    "If leak found at Schrader core, replace the core with a 1/4\" R-410A rated core (under pressure if using a core removal tool).",
    "If leak is at a brazed joint, recover refrigerant, braze repair, pressure test, evacuate to 500 microns, and recharge by weight per the data plate.",
    "Weigh in refrigerant per nameplate charge (typically 5 lbs 12 oz for GSX130361). Verify subcooling hits 10\u201312\u00b0F.",
    "Run unit for 15 minutes, re-check pressures and subcooling. Confirm supply air is 55\u201360\u00b0F."
  ],
  "safety_notes": [
    "R-410A operates at significantly higher pressures than R-22 \u2014 always use 410A-rated hoses, gauges, and recovery equipment.",
    "Never vent refrigerant to atmosphere \u2014 EPA Section 608 violation.",
    "Wear safety glasses when connecting gauges \u2014 liquid slugging can cause frostbite.",
    "If you suspect a large leak (>30% charge lost), check compressor oil level before recharging."
  ],
  "estimated_minutes": 60,
  "tags": [
    "refrigerant",
    "low charge",
    "R-410A",
    "won't cool",
    "warm suction",
    "subcooling",
    "superheat",
    "goodman",
    "GSX13",
    "leak"
  ],
